2. Scope — the GS2D file format is NOT covered
----------------------------------------------

The source code of gstextconv is open source under the terms in Section 1.
The GS2D container (files with extensions such as ".gs2d" or ".ast" used by
FS20, FS23 and related titles), and the game assets distributed
in that format, are proprietary works of their respective owners and are
NOT licensed under this document.

The permissions granted in Section 1 cover only the Software itself. They
do NOT, and cannot, grant:

  (a) any right, title, license or interest in or to the GS2D file format,
      its specification, trademarks, service marks, logos, or trade dress;

  (b) any right to the texture data, images, meshes, audio, or any other
      assets that may be stored inside GS2D files or any other container
      consumed or produced by this Software;

  (c) any right to reverse engineer, modify, distribute, or use such
      assets, format specifications, or associated intellectual property
      of any third party.

The Software is released strictly for the purposes of interoperability and
independent study of file format structure, to the extent permitted by
applicable law in the user's jurisdiction.


